thread.title_full: U.S. Government Bonds Strengthen on Dudley’s Remarks - WSJ

author: Min Zeng
title: U.S. Government Bonds Strengthen on Dudley’s Remarks
text:
U.S. Treasury bonds strengthened and clawed back earlier price losses after a top Federal Reserve official said the case was less compelling for the central bank to raise interest rates in September.
Bond prices had fallen on a strong business spending report, but buyers stepped into the bond market after William Dudley, president of the Federal Reserve Bank of New York, said international developments have increased downside risk for the U.S. economy.
